==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Casehardened
<hw>Case"hard`ened</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the surface hardened, as iron tools.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hardened against, or insusceptible to, good
influences; rendered callous by persistence in wrongdoing or resistance
of good influences; -- said of persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Casehardening</ent>⟦br⟧
